55:39.720 --> 55:41.085
Let him race!

55:41.240 --> 55:42.605
Let him race!

55:42.760 --> 55:44.000
Let him race!

55:44.160 --> 55:47.289
Let him race! Let him race!
Let him race!

55:49.440 --> 55:51.966
Now, now. Order.

55:52.160 --> 55:53.571
Sir, if I may.

55:53.720 --> 55:55.927
You might want to
get a two-shot here.

55:56.120 --> 56:01.729
I, like this passionate gentleman
here, came from humble beginnings.

56:01.920 --> 56:04.730
In the words of my dear father,

56:04.920 --> 56:10.370
"No dream is too big,
and no dreamer, too small."

56:11.000 --> 56:12.889
And that is why I, for one,

56:13.040 --> 56:17.364
believe that if the Indy 500 isn't
going to put a limit on speed,

56:17.560 --> 56:21.121
then it shouldn't
put a limit on spirit!

56:22.280 --> 56:24.248
Give the people what they want.

56:24.440 --> 56:26.010
Let him race!

56:26.160 --> 56:30.768
Let him race! Let him race!
Let him race!

56:30.920 --> 56:32.251
Just me.

56:32.640 --> 56:34.051
Whole frame, my face.

56:37.480 --> 56:38.766
All right!

56:40.920 --> 56:42.763
"All right," what?

56:43.400 --> 56:47.291
Your snail can compete
in the Indianapolis 500.

56:49.400 --> 56:50.481
Yeah!

56:50.800 --> 56:54.043
Has the world lost its mind?

57:03.840 --> 57:04.999
To Turbo!

57:05.000 --> 57:07.082
Starlight Plaza! Hey!

57:07.240 --> 57:08.605
He ain't slow no more.

57:08.760 --> 57:09.839
That's for sure.

57:09.840 --> 57:10.959
Shut the door.

57:10.960 --> 57:12.724
Get on the floor.

57:12.880 --> 57:14.723
Barbeque sauce!

57:16.040 --> 57:17.804
<i>And we're back
with more from Indianapolis.</i>

57:17.960 --> 57:19.689
Check it out.
We're on TV.

57:19.840 --> 57:21.519
<i>Mr. Lopez,
how do you feel about</i>

57:21.520 --> 57:23.090
<i>getting to compete
in the Indy 500?</i>

57:23.240 --> 57:25.322
<i>I'm just so happy.</i>

57:25.480 --> 57:27.399
<i>And we'd all be
happy to see you</i>

57:27.400 --> 57:29.243
<i>come on down to
the Starlight Plaza.</i>

57:29.400 --> 57:32.449
<i>Just north of the 101
in Van Nuys, California.</i>

57:32.600 --> 57:36.366
<i>Kim Ly Nail Salon. Where we
put the "nail" in "snail. "</i>

57:37.360 --> 57:40.603
Taco Man cried in front of
millions of people. Ow!

58:02.600 --> 58:04.648
Here you go, Paz.
Nice and warm.

58:04.800 --> 58:05.847
Goodnight, Tito.

58:05.960 --> 58:07.644
You comfy enough, Bobby?
Uh... No.

58:07.800 --> 58:09.325
Okay, let me know
if you need anything.

58:09.480 --> 58:11.403
Hey! No touching!

58:14.080 --> 58:16.003
Smooth, smooth, smooth.

58:16.920 --> 58:21.323
Sleep tight, Little Amigo.
We got a big day tomorrow.

58:22.800 --> 58:24.290
Yep.

58:25.080 --> 58:27.242
Big day, indeed.

58:27.360 --> 58:30.443
Hmm, I'm detecting a refreshing
note of disapproval.

58:30.600 --> 58:33.649
I'm worried.
And you should be, too.

58:33.920 --> 58:35.079
I'll be fine.

58:35.080 --> 58:38.439
You are delusional,
you know that?

58:38.440 --> 58:41.125
It's Big Red all over again.

58:41.760 --> 58:43.967
Only this time, instead
of one lawn mower,

58:44.160 --> 58:48.609
it'll be 32 giant,
fire-breathing cars!

58:49.600 --> 58:51.489
And I won't be
able to save you.

58:51.640 --> 58:55.008
You won't have to, because
this time, I have speed.

58:55.160 --> 58:58.289
You're not a car.
You're a snail.

58:58.880 --> 59:03.010
I got a shot here, Chet.
I can do this. You'll see.

59:03.160 --> 59:04.571
No, I won't.

59:04.960 --> 59:08.885
I will not stand by and watch
the only brother I've got

59:09.040 --> 59:13.364
risk his life chasing
some impossible dream.

59:13.960 --> 59:15.689
I'm sorry, Theo.

59:19.320 --> 59:21.800
All of these people,
they believe in me.

59:22.520 --> 59:25.603
Guy Gagne believes in me.

59:26.280 --> 59:28.248
Why won't you?

59:28.400 --> 59:32.166
And by the way,
my name is Turbo.

01:00:00.040 --> 01:00:02.407
All right.
<i>Tout suite</i>, let's go.

01:00:12.520 --> 01:00:13.681
Whoa.

01:00:14.480 --> 01:00:17.484
2.2-liter turbo V6.

01:00:17.880 --> 01:00:20.611
24-valve
quad-overhead cam.

01:00:21.200 --> 01:00:24.399
Fastest open-wheel, single-seat
machine on the planet.

01:00:24.400 --> 01:00:27.210
I think I'm in love.

01:00:29.120 --> 01:00:30.724
No way.

01:00:39.600 --> 01:00:42.410
You're not trying to steal
my trophy from me, are you?

01:00:45.560 --> 01:00:49.610
Because if you want one for
yourself, you may have a long wait.

01:00:49.760 --> 01:00:50.841
Espresso?

01:00:51.880 --> 01:00:56.044
So, you are my
little competition, eh?

01:00:56.200 --> 01:00:58.567
The underdog
versus the champion.

01:00:58.720 --> 01:01:01.803
The world loves the
underdogs, you know.

01:01:01.960 --> 01:01:04.850
The dreamers out there,
they need them.

01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:07.399
Need to believe
that one day, maybe

01:01:07.400 --> 01:01:09.687
they could achieve
the impossible, too.

01:01:12.480 --> 01:01:17.008
Well, the sad truth is,
underdogs seldom win.

01:01:18.400 --> 01:01:19.925
And dreamers?

01:01:20.080 --> 01:01:23.129
Let's just say, eventually,
they have to wake up.

01:01:26.040 --> 01:01:31.331
I've never talked to a snail before.
So small, so amusing.

01:01:31.480 --> 01:01:33.801
No wonder they want
to see you race, eh?

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:36.526
Vroom! Vroom!

01:01:36.680 --> 01:01:38.523
Look at him go.

01:01:38.680 --> 01:01:40.489
Thank you, plucky snail.

01:01:40.640 --> 01:01:45.487
Because of you, the whole world
will be watching this race.

01:01:45.680 --> 01:01:50.891
And when the checkered flag drops,
they'll be watching me win.

01:01:55.520 --> 01:01:57.761
Crawl home, garden snail,

01:02:00.800 --> 01:02:02.802
while you still can.

01:02:06.120 --> 01:02:08.043
<i>Good afternoon, race fans,</i>

01:02:08.240 --> 01:02:12.484
and welcome to this year's
running of the Indianapolis 500.

01:02:12.640 --> 01:02:14.847
<i>Televised in over 200 countries</i>

01:02:14.960 --> 01:02:17.122
<i>and aired in
33 different languages,</i>

01:02:17.280 --> 01:02:18.964
<i>this is no longer just a race,</i>

01:02:19.120 --> 01:02:22.249
<i>this is the day you'll be telling
your grandchildren about.</i>

01:02:24.880 --> 01:02:29.249
<i>Where were you the day they let
a snail race in the Indy 500?</i>

01:02:30.840 --> 01:02:32.968
Okay, time to go.
You ready?

01:02:41.360 --> 01:02:43.681
All right, team meeting.
Bring it in.

01:02:43.920 --> 01:02:48.164
This is it, Little Amigo.
This is our moment. Our time.

01:02:48.320 --> 01:02:50.846
Today is the day
we make our mark.

01:02:53.280 --> 01:02:56.011
Everybody in!
It's go time!

01:03:02.480 --> 01:03:06.644
Oh, Theo.
Be careful out there.

01:03:07.640 --> 01:03:09.722
Hey, little snail.
Are you lost?

01:03:09.880 --> 01:03:10.959
No.

01:03:10.960 --> 01:03:13.279
Are you a boy, or a girl?

01:03:13.280 --> 01:03:16.682
